  "texts": [
    "Kand mitigate cybersecurity risks collectively 8.",
    "The AI Act introduces a voluntary AI conformity assessment framework, which may include cybersecurity criteria.",
    "The framework allows AI systems to obtain certification to demonstrate their compliance with the Act's requirements, including cybersecurity measures 9.",
    "The AI Act designates supervisory authorities responsible for overseeing compliance with the Act's provisions, including cybersecurity requirements.",
    "The authorities will have the power to audit, assess, and enforce compliance with the measures outlined in the Act-aspects of the approach have similarities to what was proposed by the Malta Digital Innovation Authority [13].The AI act categorises AI systems into four risk levels: unacceptable risk 10, high risk, limited risk, and minimal risk."
  ]
